<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-08-26T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-08-26T18:00:00-05:00" n="408" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d408">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/14306:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-08-26T19:00:00-04:00">August 26, 1941—7
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>149. Your 311, August 24, noon. Please keep Department promptly
                                informed on Turkish reaction to Anglo-Russian invasion of Iran, and
                                what effect, if any, this is likely to have on Turkey’s future
                                attitude toward Britain and the Axis.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>